FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">couple ideas for new spells</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I had a few ideas for some new spells.  I apologize if these have already been mentioned....<br>
<br>
First I think some more O'kiels spells would be cool.  BUT, not in the traditional damage shield sense.  Instead what about some soft of magic reflection series of spells.  Basically if a mob nuked whoever this spell was cast on, some of that damage would be reflected back at the casting mob.  This would also mean that the targer takes less damage since some has been reflected.  Perhaps add a self only version similar to the necro harmshield where the wizzy is immune to all forms of magic attact for 20 seconds or something.<br>
<br>
Second idea.  perhaps have a spell called form of the Pheonix or something.  Effect would be illusion Phoenix(not necessary but cool side effect), caster movement rate to zero, and the caster breaths small fire blasts every few seconds for the duration of the spell (4 minutes?).  this would be dangerous, since you wouldnt be able to cast other spells during this period, and you cant run away.  But it would allow us to do more damage over a longer fight against a velious ubermob.<br>
<br>
Next an upgrade to the fade/shadow step series of spells.  But instead of a random distance random direction how about one that move the wizard X distance in a straight line.<br>
<br>
Speaking of upgrade, upgrades to resistant skin, and elemental armor might be nice....<br>
<br>
How about a spell or better yet a skill to detect what form of direct damage a mob is most vulnerable to.  Detect Resistance or something.  All it would report back is You think TARGET_01 is most vulnerable to FIRE.  or ICE or MAGIC.  <br>
<br>
OK last idea.  I know this one may cause me some negative feedback, but here goes anyway.  I think we should get DoT spells.  It just fits to have a Napalm type spell.  Where your target gets a nasty DD blast, and then continues to burn, or continues to freeze.  Im undeceided if we should get magic based DoT or not.  I know druids already have some of these kinds of spells, and shammys and necros are the masters of DoTs.  Im not suggesting upsetting that balance.  <br>
<br>
Anyway those are my thoughts for the day.  Flame me if ya like im just brainstorming though =)<br>
<br>
Emirkal<br>
57th Evoker<br>
<br>
Just some thoughts....<br>
